msgid ""
"When you next open your eyes, you are back in the bed of your hotel room. You raise your hand to shield your eyes from the sunlight that pierces through the bedroomΟΔβ²§β³Δs curtains. The glaring light is akin to a vice crushing your temples. Thin wisps of incense smoke fill the air.\n"
"Rising to your feet requires a colossal effort. A small voice in the back of your mind tells you it was all a figment of your imagination, a nightmare fueled by weariness. It is the voice of self-preservation warning you to avoid the path of lunacy you have set upon. You ignore it and rise to your feet, your legs trembling with terror and exhaustion. Quietly, you call out for Ichtaca, wondering if she remembers what happened last nightΟΔβ²§βÄùor if she was even there to begin with. You find her slumped on the floor, her back against the door of the hotel room. She is unconscious and unresponsive, her face ashen. After several worrisome minutes attempting to wake her, you finally succeed. She sputters into consciousness, coughing violently and convulsing as though possessed. ΟΔβ²§≈™The cave. The maw in the sky, bathed in red. Did you see it?ΟΔβ²§¬ù\n"
"Your head pulses with pain as you attempt to remember the events of last night, and you shake your head. ΟΔβ²§≈™It must be the path that leads to the Nexus,ΟΔβ²§¬ù she continues, gripping her head tightly with one hand. You attempt to help her to her feet, but she pushes you away. ΟΔβ²§≈™What was I thinking? The boundary is thinning. Any tension and it could have snapped.ΟΔβ²§¬ù Her gaze shifts toward you. ΟΔβ²§≈™I should not have involved you in this. But, like it or not, you are involved. It is too late to go back. I know where to find the Nexus, and you must journey with me.ΟΔβ²§¬ù"
msgstr ""
"Quando vocΟΣ abre os olhos, estΟΓ de volta na cama de seu quarto de hotel. VocΟΣ levanta sua mΟΘo para proteger os olhos da luz do sol que atravessa as cortinas do quarto. A luz intensa Ο© como uma prensa esmagando suas tΟΣmporas. Finos fios de fumaΟßa de incenso preenchem o ar.\n"
"Ficar de pΟ© Ο© um esforΟßo colossal. Uma fraca voz num canto da sua mente diz que foi tudo fruto da sua imaginaΟßΟΘo, um pesadelo alimentado pelo cansaΟßo. Οâ a voz da autopreservaΟßΟΘo avisando-o para evitar o caminho lunΟΓtico que vocΟΣ escolheu. VocΟΣ a ignora e se levanta, suas pernas tremendo de terror e exaustΟΘo. Silenciosamente, vocΟΣ chama por Ichtaca, pensando se ela se lembra do que aconteceu na noite anterior βÄî ou se ela estava mesmo lΟΓ para inΟ≠cio de conversa. VocΟΣ a encontra caΟ≠da no chΟΘo, as costas apoiadas na porta do quarto de hotel. Ela estΟΓ inconsciente e nΟΘo responde, seu rosto pΟΓlido. ApΟ≥s vΟΓrios minutos de preocupaΟßΟΘo tentando acordΟΓ-la, vocΟΣ finalmente consegue. Ela recobra a consciΟΣncia, tossindo violentamente e convulsionando como se estivesse possuΟ≠da. βÄ€A caverna. A boca no cΟ©u, banhada de vermelho. VocΟΣ a viu?βÄù\n"
